<item>
            <title>[WICKET-4696] NumberTextField doesn&apos;t accept values &lt;=0 for Double and Float</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/WICKET-4696</link>
                <project id="12310561" key="WICKET">Wicket</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The org.apache.wicket.util.lang.Numbers class defines the method :&lt;br/&gt;
public static Number getMinValue(Class&amp;lt;? extends Number&amp;gt; numberType)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This method return the MatchingNumberTypeClass.MIN_VALUE.&lt;br/&gt;
But for Double.MIN_VALUE and Float.MIN_VALUE return the smallest positive number, not the smallest negative number like for the other number classes.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;One side effect is that by default you can&apos;t enter a negative value, or a 0 in a NumberTextField&amp;lt;Double&amp;gt; or NumberTextField&amp;lt;Float&amp;gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
